@node Usage
===============================
 Usage
===============================

Quite simple really ;-)

First, ensure the ToolTypes of the PalmSync icon are correct for
your set-up:

 DIR (defaults to RAM:)

	Directory to use for backups/restores.

 DEVICE (defaults to serial.device)

	Appropriate serial device (I'd recommend using
        artser.device for the internal serial port).

 UNIT (defaults to 0)

	Unit number of the serial device.

 MAXBAUD (defaults to 57600)

	Maximum transfer rate to use. 57600 is the limit for
        pretty much all standard Palm units.



Double click on the icon to open up the interface. At present
you'll find four buttons... and a decorative icon which serves no
purpose except to detract from a dull interface ;-) Ensure your
Palm device is placed into its cradle before use...

 Backup

	Dumps the contents of the Palm device to RAM: or the
        directory specified in the ToolTypes.

 Install

	Pops up a file requester, and then installs the specified
        file to the Palm device

 List

	Lists all the databases stored on the Palm device

 Restore

	Restores the contents of a backup directory to the Palm
        device


If you've used PalmTransfer you should be familiar with these main
options.

@endnode
